Here’s a purpose-built emoji guide — each with a specific meaning tailored to off-market wholesaling, buyers, and renovations:
🏠 Properties (General Use)
🏠 House → Standard single-family property (baseline marker)
🏡 House w/ garden → Family-ready, suburban property w/ yard potential
🏚️ Derelict house → Fixer-upper, distressed, foreclosure, heavy rehab lead
🏘️ Houses → Multi-family units, duplex/triplex, or rental clusters
🏙️ Cityscape → Condo/apartment opportunities in Minneapolis/St. Paul
🔑 Transaction Status
📍 Pin → New lead entered (basic location marker on map)
📌 Pushpin → Hot lead (needs immediate follow-up)
🔑 Key → Under contract / locked up deal
🗝️ Old key → Closed / handed off property (sold or assigned)
🤝 Handshake → Buyer-seller agreement in progress
📝 Memo → Contract needs to be drafted or signed
💰 Money / Buyers
💵 Cash stack → Cash buyer interested
💰 Money bag → High-profit potential deal (assignment spread)
📈 Up chart → Appreciation area (long-term buy & hold opportunity)
📉 Down chart → Declining market/value (high risk, discount only)
💳 Credit card → Financing required / not cash ready
🛠️ Renovations (R3)
🛠️ Hammer & wrench → General rehab needed
🧱 Brick → Foundation/structural issues flagged
🛋️ Couch → Interior work (cosmetics, staging potential)
🪟 Window → Windows/energy updates needed
🚪 Door → Entry/security issues (locks, doors, access)
🪚 Saw → Heavy demo/tear-down candidate
🏗️ Construction crane → Major renovation / new build opportunity
🌳 Land / Lot Characteristics
🌳 Tree → Large lot / acreage (rural Minnesota properties)
🌲 Evergreen tree → Cabin/seasonal property
🌴 Palm tree → Out-of-state vacation rental (if you expand)
🚗 Car → Garage or parking availability noted
🏊 Pool → Bonus amenity (rare in MN, but high value if present)
📂 Workflow / Docs
✏️ Pencil → Property still in analysis (needs ARV/rehab calc)
🖊️ Pen → Offer written, waiting on acceptance
📄 Document → Disclosures/title paperwork in progress
🗂️ File folder → Archived deal (keep for comps or future follow-up)
🧾 Receipt → Expenses logged (inspection, utility bills, rehab cost)
📞 Communication / Outreach
📞 Phone → Call made or scheduled with seller
📧 Email → Sent follow-up or buyer’s list blast
🧭 Compass → Driving for dollars / scouting trips
🗺️ Map → Area comp check / neighborhood analysis
⚡ How to use this internally:
Use property type emojis 🏠 🏚️ 🏘️ for the main map pin.
Add status emojis 📍 🔑 📝 as tags to track where the deal sits.
Attach renovation emojis 🛠️ 🧱 🪚 as “rehab flags” when evaluating.
Use finance emojis 💵 💰 📈 to rank priority buyers + exit strategy.
Keep workflow emojis ✏️ 🖊️ 📄 for doc & contract stages.---
